JSON-RPC implementation for Perl 6


SPEC

http://json-rpc.org/wiki/specification


CLIENT

Sample connection.
GetResponse API used as an example
http://dev.getresponse.com/api-doc/

    use JSON::RPC::Client
    
    my $client = JSON::RPC::Client.new(
        host            => 'http://api2.getresponse.com',
        json_methods    => [ 'ping', 'get_campaigns' ],
    );
    
    my $response = $client.ping( 'MY_API_KEY' ); # { "ping" => "pong" }

Where≈õ

* url - is the URL of the service
* json_methods - methods that will be installed in client class,
                 this will be replaced later by CANDO autoload


